 GDIA 
 Job Description & Qualifications 
 In Global Data, Insight & Analytics (GDIA), we seek to navigate Ford Motor Company through the disruptiveness of the information age, harnessing the power of data and artificial intelligence to realize the enterprise’s known goals, reveal hidden opportunities, and achieve data superiority. 
The Strategy & Enterprise Analytics team within GDI&A is seeking a Data Scientist who can make a difference in the emerging area of people analytics at Ford. They will improve and curate new and existing data sources to build data and analytics solutions for HR. The current and future solutions that the Data Scientist helps to maintain and build include dashboards (COVID-19, Workforce, DEI, Recruiting), predictive models (e.g., attrition), AI\ML (e.g., topic modeling), and strategic/operational tools (e.g., workforce planning). The selected candidate will work directly with business partners who use the solutions and with other data scientists, data engineers, software engineers, product designers, etc. who work together throughout the data and analytics solution lifecycle. 
What you’ll be able to do: 
Understanding business opportunities and translating into analytics problem 
Formulating data and analytics solutions using a variety of data extraction and transformation processes, analytics tools and techniques, and deployment options 
Creating, testing, and deploying data and analytics solutions using skills such as data acquisition, metric development, statistical modeling, and developing prototypes with front-end and back-end components 
Introducing and strategizing use of sophisticated AI/ML techniques (e.g., NLP) in people analytics 
Collaborating across teams, tracking project progress, and communicating between technical and business groups 
Translating data-based insights into business actions and results 
Communicating to technical and non-technical audiences, cross-functional teams and executive leadership 
Providing training and maintenance of implemented tools 
The minimum requirements we seek: 
Bachelor's degree in Data Science, Computer Science, or related field 
2+ years of professional work in descriptive, predictive, and prescriptive analytics 
2+ years of experience with one or more of the following analytics tools: Python, R, Matlab, QlikView, Tableau 
2+ years of experience in distributed computing (big data) with tools like PySpark, Apache Hadoop, Hive 
2+ years of experience collaborating with teams to develop data and analytics solutions 
Our preferred requirements:
 Master’s degree 
4+ years experience in descriptive, predictive, prescriptive analytics, optimization, and AI/ML (e.g., NLP) 
4+ years of experience with Python, R, Matlab, QlikView, or Tableau 
4+ years of experience in distributed computing with PySpark, Apache Hadoop, Hive 
4+ years interacting directly with business partners and analytics solution delivery team, in diverse data and analytics applications 
Comfortable working in an environment where problems are not always well-defined 
Inquisitive, proactive, and fast in learning new analytics tools and techniques 
Strong oral, written and interpersonal communication skills 
Have a desire to excel and work with hardworking people 
What you’ll receive in return: 
As part of the Ford family, you’ll enjoy excellent compensation and a comprehensive benefits package that includes generous PTO, retirement, savings and stock investment plans, incentive compensation and much more. You’ll also experience exciting opportunities for professional and personal growth and recognition. 
If you have what it takes to help us redefine the future of mobility, we’d love to have you join us. 
Candidates for positions with Ford Motor Company must be legally authorized to work in the United States. Verification of employment eligibility will be required at the time of hire. Visa sponsorship is available for this position. 
We are an Equal Opportunity Employer committed to a culturally diverse workforce. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, religion, color, age, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability status or protected veteran status. 
For information on Ford's salary and benefits, please visit: https://corporate.ford.com/content/dam/corporate/us/en-us/documents/careers/2021-benefits-and-comp-GSR-sal-plan-1.pdf 
